âœ… 2. Installation
âœ… Requirements

Python 3.8+

Scapy installed

Admin/root permissions for packet sniffing

âœ… Install Steps
1ï¸âƒ£ Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/packet-sniffer.git
cd packet-sniffer

2ï¸âƒ£ Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

3ï¸âƒ£ Platform Requirements
âœ… Linux

Run with:

sudo python3 sniffer.py


No extra setup needed.

âœ… macOS

Install tcpdump permission:

sudo chmod +r /dev/bpf*


Run with:

sudo python3 sniffer.py

âœ… Windows

Run Command Prompt or PowerShell as Administrator.

Install Npcap (required by Scapy):

Download: https://npcap.com

âœ… 3. Usage Guide
âœ… Basic Usage
Linux/macOS:
sudo python3 sniffer.py

Windows:
python sniffer.py

âœ… Filter Examples
Filter by protocol:
sudo python3 sniffer.py --protocol tcp

Filter by IP:
sudo python3 sniffer.py --ip 192.168.1.10

Filter by port:
sudo python3 sniffer.py --port 80

âœ… Output Files
Human-readable log:
logs/captured.log

PCAP file:
captures/capture.pcap


Open PCAP file using Wireshark.

âœ… 4. Filters & Protocols
âœ… Supported Protocols
Protocol	Supported	Details
TCP	âœ…	Ports, flags, payload size
UDP	âœ…	Ports, payload size
ICMP	âœ…	Type, code
ARP	âœ…	Who-has, is-at
DNS	âœ…	Query name, type
âœ… Available Filters
Protocol Filter:
--protocol tcp
--protocol udp
--protocol icmp
--protocol arp
--protocol dns

IP Filter:
--ip <target_ip>

Port Filter:
--port <port_number>


Filters can be combined.

âœ… 5. Troubleshooting
âœ… Permission Errors
Linux/macOS:
Operation not permitted


â¡ï¸ Run using sudo

Windows:
Scapy failed to open capture interface


â¡ï¸ Install Npcap
â¡ï¸ Run PowerShell as Administrator

âœ… No Packets Captured

Try choosing a specific interface:

sudo python3 sniffer.py --iface eth0


List interfaces:

python3 - <<EOF
from scapy.all import get_if_list
print(get_if_list())
EOF

âœ… PCAP not saving

Check permissions on:

captures/


Ensure folder exists (script auto-creates).

